i18n_autoevaluation_instructions: Set the evaluation criteria by giving the percentage of total score that is required to achieve the grade.With pass/fail give the percentage required to get pass. The value is the minimum score for a grade. The same percentage cannot be given to several grades. The system cannot determine the order of the grades, so make sure you set right values.
i18n_autoevaluation_percentages_not_uniq: The percentages have to be unique
i18n_autoevaluation_release_type: Set the time when the result of the automatic evaluation will be shown to the student.
i18n_release_type_immediate: Immediately after the exam has been submitted.
i18n_release_type_given_days: Days after the exam has been submitted.
i18n_release_type_period: After the exam period has expired
i18n_autoevaluation_release_after_days: How many days after submitting the exam the result is shown
i18n_autoevaluation_release_description: The grade is generated automatically and is not final. The examiners can edit the evaluation if necessary.
i18n_speed_review_incomplete_info_or_no_: Information missing or no right to evaluate
i18n_grade_import_file_description: The CSV fields have to be <exam ID>,<grade name>,<feedback> (eg. 1234,2, Well done). Feedback is not compulsory.
i18n_create_grading_template: Create a CSV template for importing the grades.
i18n_create_grading_template_description: Student information is only to help.

i18n_no_grading_description: The exam was not given a final grade in Exam.

i18n_action_disabled_lottery_on: Action is not allowed, because it is part of randomized questions.

i18n_exam_participation_descending: Completed exams by date (oldest one first)

i18n_review_no_result: No results in search for completed exams
i18n_exam_no_started: No completed exams to be evaluated

i18n_exam_library_no_results: No results in search for questions

i18n_exam_participants_description: Students that the exam has been assigned to. A student must be logged in to examination service in order to be found with Search function. After publishing the exam an email will be sent to students.
i18n_exam_validity_description: Exam period is a period for students for taking the exam. Students can book an exam which has time period valid or in the future. The period for taking the exam can be extended with no limits. Exam period can not be shortened if there are reservations for the exam.
i18n_exam_duration_description: The duration of the exam means the time that a student has for taking the exam. Exam time starts running when the time of reservation begins. If a student arrives late to an exam, exam time is already running.
i18n_exam_section_order_description: The number of the section. In exam there can be 1 to N sections, in which the sets of questions are included. The sections are visible to students in a student's view.
i18n_exam_section_description_descriptio: The description of the section. You can give instructions regarding questions of this section here.
i18n_exam_section_randomize_description: Question randomization is available within the section if the questions are equal. If randomization is in use, the chosen amount of questions will be drawn randomly for students. If the randomization is not in use, questions can not be added before taking off the randomization temporarily. Previous exams or other correlations will not be taken into consideration.
i18n_additional_info_for_registry_descri: Additional information that can be transferred to an external information system of studies
i18n_send_to_other_reviewers_description: A message to other assessors about assessment.
i18n_question_text_description: Add question text. You can edit the text with the text editor. You can define additional information after choosing the question type.
i18n_question_type_description: Choosing the question type. Essay: answering by writing or attaching a file. Multiple choice question (one correct answer): define many choices, one correct. Multiple choice question (many correct answer): define many choices, at least one correct. Fill-in question: define 1-n gaps. Student answers by filling in gaps. Statement question (can be edited): Define three answer options, default options are True/False/I don't know. The text and points of True and False options can be edited. Minus points reduce the total points of the exam.
i18n_question_owners_description: The owners of the question have full rights to edit the question even if it is used in an exam of another owner
i18n_attachment_description: A file that a student can download in an exam. Make sure that software needed for opening the file is available on computers
i18n_question_instruction_description: Additional information for students on answering the questions during the exam
i18n_question_tag_question_description: You can categorize and find the the questions by using key words
i18n_question_evaluation_criteria_descri: Assessment criteria that helps in assessing the question. Criteria is shown with the assessment of the answer.
i18n_select_exam_course_description: Choose the course that exam is related to. Use the course code of the whole course if needed. It is possible to change the code before publishing the exam.
i18n_enrolment_url_description: Link to a student for registration for this exam. A student can also search for exam by name of the exam.
i18n_exam_title_description: Name of the exam that is shown after the course information. For example Mid-exam 1.
i18n_exam_credit_type_description: The exam is a whole course study attainment. The exam is a partial course study attainment and the grade is for this partial course study attainment
i18n_exam_grade_scale_description: Exam grading scale. The grading scale can be integrated to the grading scale of the course especially in whole course study attainments.
i18n_exam_instruction_description: Instructions are shown to the student when the exam begins. The student can also view the instructions during the exam.
i18n_exam_enroll_instruction_description: Instructions are shown to the student when making a reservation
i18n_exam_review_attachment_description: Downloads the attached files of the exams that haven't been assessed and sorts them to files for assessment elsewhere.
i18n_aborted_description: List of students who have returned an empty exam paper / aborted the exam.
i18n_review_started_description: List of the completed exams that have not been graded
i18n_graded_description: List of the completed exams that have been graded manually or automatically. You can still edit assessments. Student can't see assessment before it is locked.
i18n_graded_logged_description: List of the completed exams that are locked and ready to be registered in the study systems either automatically or manually. You can't edit assessments anymore. Student can see assessment.
i18n_new_exam_type_description: Choose the exam type. General exams are available for all students. A personal exam can be assigned to 1 to n students.
i18n_error_autoevaluation_essay_question: It is not possible to add an essay question to an exam that will be assessed automatically
i18n_action_disabled_minimum_options: A question in a published exam has to have at least one correct option
i18n_language_inspection_setting_not_cho: Please go back to basic information to select if language evaluation is needed or not.
i18n_inspection_comment_info: Write a message to the other evaluator/examiner (not visible for students)
i18n_maturity_search_description: You can filter results by course code, exam name, student name or by examiner name.
i18n_exam_pre_participants: Inform a participant who has not logged in to the service.
i18n_exam_pre_participants_description: You can inform the participants who have not logged in to the service about the exam. EXAM will send an email when the exam is published. After this they can log in to the service and make a reservation for the exam.
i18n_question_review_info: Choose here the questions to be graded.
i18n_question_review_info_detailed: The questions are shown here according to the order in the exam. Deleted questions are at the end of the list. Please note that you can only choose essay questions for assessment by questions.
i18n_additional_info_for_student: Additional information for a locked assessment (shown to the student).
i18n_additional_info_for_student_descrip: Locked assessment cannot be changed. Inform the student if the assessment has been changed afterwards. The information is shown to the student.
i18n_question_differs: The question that the student has answered has a different wording than the current one.
i18n_pre_publish_exam_confirm: Are you sure you want to pre-publish the exam? After this the teachers are able to edit the exam.
i18n_collaborative_exam_response_search_: You can search the joint exam attainments by exam name.
i18n_exam_material_description: Exam questions based on this exam material/content
i18n_optional_section_description: Student can select, if he/she wants to take the optional section. The choice is made when booking the exam time. In the exam, the student will not see the questions of the optional sections he/she has not chosen.
i18n_select_optional_section: I want to take this section
i18n_confirm_external_reservation: When you book an exam visit, you agree to comply with the host university's EXAM terms of use and surveillance practices. University-specific terms of use and exam visit instructions are available on each university's website.
i18n_external_reservation_link_text: Read instructions and terms of use (e-exam.fi)
i18n_seb_exam_about_to_begin: You have a Safe Exam Browser exam starting at
i18n_seb_exam_ongoing: You have a Safe Exam Browser exam going on. To start the exam, please log back in with the SEB file that you received as attachment of the booking confimation email.
i18n_quit_seb: Click this link to exit the Safe Exam Browser. You can use your computer after this normally.
i18n_exam_amount_questions: Randomized questions in the exam (all questions in the exam)
i18n_exam_grade_time: Total score in relation to session time
i18n_settings_password: Password for an exam event (to be revealed to students at the beginning of exam event)
i18n_examination_events_description: It is possible to take BYOD exams in the exam event.
i18n_examination_type_description: EXAM room: exam taken in a room with video surveillance . Restricted BYOD (SEB): Bring Your Own Device exam taken with a Safe Exam Browser somewhere else than in a room with video surveillance. Unrestricted BYOD = Bring Your Own Device exam taken somewhere else than in a room with video surveillance.
i18n_enrolments_exist_for_examination_ev: The date, time or passwords cannot be edited because there are already registrations for the exam event.
i18n_collaborative_exam_search_descripti: You can search exams by exam name. Type at least three letters to begin search.
i18n_claim_choice_question_instruction: Statement question (can be edited): Student can get negative points for a wrong answer which will affect the total points of the exam. However, the total points cannot go below zero. Default answer options are: True, False and I don't know. Student will see the answer options in this order (it will not be randomized).
i18n_claim_choice_options_description: Correct and wrong answer is determined by the score per answer option (>0 correct and <=0 wrong):
i18n_claim_choice_correct_points_descrip: The score for a correct answer is always more than zero (>0)
i18n_claim_choice_incorrect_points_descr: The score for a wrong answer is always zero or less (<=0)
i18n_claim_choice_skip_option_descriptio: The score for an I don't know answer is always zero points and you can't modify the answer text.
i18n_collaborative_exam_search_descripti: You can search by exam name or teacher's email
i18n_export_questions: Export questions to Moodle XML format (only essays and multiple choice questions)
i18n_event_enrolments_exist: It is not possible to delete the exam event, because there are registrations for the event.
i18n_evaluation_select_amount_descriptio: Number of Pass / Fail questions in the section.
i18n_exam_name_description: The current name of the exam (the previous names are not shown).
i18n_course_name_description: Study module or realization (previous modules or realizations not shown).
i18n_exam_validity_period_description: The exam period when the exam is or has been open for students.
i18n_exam_amount_questions_description: Randomized questions now included in this exam compared to all questions available in all sections.
i18n_exam_amount_reservations_descriptio: How many attainments have been assessed at the moment (no-shows, aborted exams or upcoming registrations not counted in).
i18n_feedback_summary_description: The number of feedback of locked assessments that has been read and the number of feedback given. (NB! Only the locked assessments are shown here.) NB! The feedback and grade have to be locked, not just saved, to be shown here.
i18n_exam_grade_distribution_description: Distribution of saved and locked assessments (both shown here).
i18n_save_changes_popover_info: Save the assessment as unfinished. The assessment can still be changed if exam grade is not yet given.
i18n_send_result_to_registry_popover_inf: The exam grade has to be given before the assessment can be locked. When locked you cannot change the assessment anymore and the student will be sent an email about the assessment.
i18n_missing_examination_event_configura: Exam event is missing, you cannot publish the exam. Go back to the Publish tab and add an exam event.
i18n_section_averages: Average of points of exam sections
i18n_section_averages_tooltip: Average of points of the exam sections/Maximum points for the section
i18n_transfer_questions: Copy the questions for yourself to another EXAM system
i18n_exam_room_accessibility: Accessibility requirements for the exam room
i18n_move_section: Change the order of the exam sections by dragging
i18n_selected_sections: Exam sections which have been chosen for this exam
i18n_days_since_period_beginning: Days since the exam period started.
